WEBVTT

00:04.182 --> 00:05.080
Look at him.

00:05.081 --> 00:07.520
So engaged in his
electronic television game.

00:07.521 --> 00:08.987
More like obsessed.

00:08.988 --> 00:11.623
He needs to stop for five
minutes and clean up his room.

00:11.624 --> 00:15.460
Which one of us do you
think they're talking about?

00:15.461 --> 00:17.229
My room's clean.

00:17.230 --> 00:18.730
Gotta be you.

00:18.731 --> 00:21.466
Honestly, I don't know what
you two see in that game.

00:21.467 --> 00:23.569
"That game" is Chimpocalypse,

00:23.570 --> 00:25.804
the most popular video game in America.

00:25.805 --> 00:28.807
And hamburger sandwiches
are the most popular food.

00:28.808 --> 00:30.708
Doesn't make them good.

00:31.710 --> 00:33.946
Okay, Evan, time to do your homework.

00:33.947 --> 00:35.080
Aw, man.

00:35.081 --> 00:36.864
Oscar, you need to get
cleaned up for dinner.

00:36.865 --> 00:38.030
Aw, man.

00:39.084 --> 00:40.319
Thank you.

00:40.320 --> 00:42.521
I know you and Evan got
off to a rocky start,

00:42.522 --> 00:45.023
I really appreciate how hard
you've worked to win him over.

00:45.024 --> 00:47.292
The key is putting myself
in the mind of a child.

00:47.293 --> 00:49.794
Well, feel free to
come back out any time.

00:51.797 --> 00:54.233
All right, I want a
re-match, buddy, tomorrow.

00:54.234 --> 00:55.900
It's your money.

00:59.204 --> 01:00.872
Hey, Charlotte! Cute top.

01:00.873 --> 01:04.042
Thanks, Teddy.

01:04.043 --> 01:06.811
Women love to hear about their shirts.

01:08.080 --> 01:10.782
Hey, you guys mind if I brought
Andre over here for Halloween?

01:10.783 --> 01:12.818
He heard this building is
great for trick-or-treating.

01:12.819 --> 01:14.899
Of course. Although I'm not
sure where he heard that,

01:14.900 --> 01:16.363
we hardly get any trick-or-treaters.

01:16.364 --> 01:17.322
Well, we used to.

01:17.323 --> 01:19.625
Then Felix moved in, and
instead of giving them candy,

01:19.626 --> 01:21.792
he gave out dental floss.

01:22.562 --> 01:24.830
Are you saying that children
are avoiding our apartment?

01:24.831 --> 01:25.831
No.

01:25.832 --> 01:27.231
They're avoiding you.

01:28.400 --> 01:30.968
Evan told me they all
call you Count Plaque-ula.

01:31.937 --> 01:33.605
Count Plaque-ula.

01:33.606 --> 01:36.275
Kids are mean and funny.

01:36.276 --> 01:37.676
Laugh all you want,

01:37.677 --> 01:39.244
but gingivitis doesn't take a holiday.

01:39.245 --> 01:41.388
A little fact that Big Candy
doesn't want you to know.

01:41.389 --> 01:43.348
Felix, come on.

01:43.349 --> 01:44.983
Halloween is the one night of the year

01:44.984 --> 01:47.019
you get to go crazy and be a kid.

01:47.020 --> 01:48.287
Is it?

01:48.288 --> 01:50.389
Or is it just a celebration
of irresponsibility?

01:50.390 --> 01:53.424
"Let's get hopped up on
sugar and mock the dead!"

01:55.160 --> 01:57.229
You got pushed down a
lot as a kid, didn't you?

01:57.230 --> 01:58.530
Face it, Felix,

01:58.531 --> 02:00.299
Halloween isn't the problem... you are.

02:00.300 --> 02:02.334
You just don't know how to cut loose.

02:02.335 --> 02:04.202
Can't cut loose? I?

02:04.203 --> 02:07.639
The guy who plays "La
Vida Loca" on the cello?

02:07.640 --> 02:11.076
I feel like pushing him down right now.

02:11.077 --> 02:12.244
Are you actually saying

02:12.245 --> 02:13.912
that I lack a childlike
sense of abandon?

02:13.913 --> 02:15.314
You were never a child.

02:15.315 --> 02:18.750
When you came out of the
womb, you hung up the placenta.

02:18.751 --> 02:20.385
Well, I'm not going

02:20.386 --> 02:23.055
to apologize for being a mature adult.

02:23.056 --> 02:24.956
As the poet William
Butler Yeats famously said,

02:24.957 --> 02:25.991
"It is so many years..."

02:25.992 --> 02:28.159
Oh, you going down right now!

02:31.196 --> 02:32.831
Damn, you're like a statue!

02:32.832 --> 02:34.331
Pilates.

02:35.572 --> 02:39.033
<font color="#33FF00">Subtitle sync and corrections by
<b>awaqeded</b> for <b>www.addic7ed.com.</b></font>

02:41.106 --> 02:42.842
I don't believe it.

02:42.843 --> 02:44.376
Where'd that come from?

02:44.377 --> 02:46.480
I hung it while you were
at work, I hope you like it.

02:46.481 --> 02:49.315
Aw, I love a Halloween decoration!

02:51.750 --> 02:53.584
Or every one ever made.

02:54.887 --> 02:56.188
Oh, is it too much?

02:56.189 --> 02:58.457
Oh, I'm sorry. You've
already been so nice

02:58.458 --> 03:00.726
by letting me crash here
while I find a new apartment.

03:00.727 --> 03:02.361
No, no, no, it's the perfect setting

03:02.362 --> 03:03.660
for our scary movie marathon.

03:03.661 --> 03:04.995
Ooh, I can't wait!

03:04.996 --> 03:07.498
But you know what, I've got to warn you,

03:07.499 --> 03:09.399
when I get scared I have to pee,

03:09.400 --> 03:11.601
so we're going to be
working that pause button.

03:12.603 --> 03:13.770
Hello.

03:13.771 --> 03:18.308
Oh, what a festive
display of fire hazards.

03:18.309 --> 03:20.332
Oh that's right, Halloween
isn't really your thing.

03:20.333 --> 03:21.611
No, never has been.

03:21.612 --> 03:23.513
I remember the last time
I tried to participate.

03:23.514 --> 03:24.982
I was seven and dressed

03:24.983 --> 03:27.116
as Nobel-Prize-winning
scientist Marie Curie.

03:28.185 --> 03:30.686
Had to take off my pumps
to escape the bullies.

03:31.855 --> 03:33.790
Oh, sweetie.

03:33.791 --> 03:36.727
Why are you not trying
to repress that memory?

03:36.728 --> 03:40.297
Well, Oscar pointed out
that apparently I lack

03:40.298 --> 03:43.166
a sense of childlike whimsy.

03:43.167 --> 03:44.868
Since when do you
care what Oscar thinks?

03:44.869 --> 03:47.237
Since when does Oscar
use the word "whimsy?"

03:47.238 --> 03:49.272
Well, it's not just Oscar.

03:49.273 --> 03:51.575
I was upset to learn that
the children of the building

03:51.576 --> 03:53.759
seem to agree. I guess it's
because I don't know how to

03:53.760 --> 03:56.046
"cut loose" or "go crazy."

03:56.047 --> 03:58.849
Those air quotes aren't
doing you any favors.

03:58.850 --> 04:01.184
Well, this year I plan to embrace

04:01.185 --> 04:02.853
the spirit of the season,

04:02.854 --> 04:04.588
by planning a good, old fashioned,

04:04.589 --> 04:06.490
night of irresponsible fun.

04:06.491 --> 04:09.091
How about you just put
your hands in your pockets?

04:10.127 --> 04:12.062
Good for you. What do you have in mind?

04:12.063 --> 04:13.397
Well, as you know,

04:13.398 --> 04:15.732
every Halloween there is
a kids' party in the lobby.

04:15.733 --> 04:17.733
But this year, as board president,

04:17.735 --> 04:20.370
I plan to introduce a haunted history

04:20.370 --> 04:21.571
tour of the building.

04:21.572 --> 04:23.073
And I'm here because

04:23.074 --> 04:26.510
I need some spooky helpers.

04:26.511 --> 04:27.944
We actually have plans.

04:27.945 --> 04:30.547
Yeah, we're going to eat
popcorn, watch scary movies,

04:30.548 --> 04:32.781
and not pee on the couch.

04:34.117 --> 04:35.751
But you could do that any night!

04:36.153 --> 04:37.154
Please?

04:37.155 --> 04:38.789
It would really mean a lot to me.

04:38.790 --> 04:41.925
Aw, who could say no to this face?

04:41.926 --> 04:42.925
I could.

04:44.494 --> 04:46.229
But I won't.

04:46.230 --> 04:47.253
But I could.

04:47.254 --> 04:49.266
Well, fantastic!

04:49.267 --> 04:51.168
I will get you a draft of the script

04:51.169 --> 04:52.512
so that you can start memorizing.

04:52.513 --> 04:53.679
Oh god! Oh no!

04:54.738 --> 04:56.678
Oh, I love Halloween,
so much fun, so much fun.

04:57.808 --> 04:59.141
- Hey.
- Hey.

05:00.477 --> 05:02.245
Oh, cool chimpbot costume!

05:02.246 --> 05:04.581
I wish they made those in adult sizes.

05:04.582 --> 05:05.982
Maybe they do.

05:05.983 --> 05:08.150
No, I already checked.

05:10.420 --> 05:13.523
You are gonna clean
up on candy tomorrow.

05:13.524 --> 05:15.125
Not here I'm not.

05:15.126 --> 05:16.793
I have to work tomorrow night,

05:16.794 --> 05:17.794
so Evan's going

05:17.795 --> 05:19.496
to my sister's in Long Island.

05:19.497 --> 05:22.799
Or he could stay here and
go trick-or-treating with me.

05:22.800 --> 05:24.601
That's what I said!

05:24.602 --> 05:27.403
But then my mom just laughed
for, like, a really long time.

05:28.438 --> 05:31.675
I didn't laugh... that long.

05:31.676 --> 05:35.011
What's so funny about
me taking care of Evan?

05:35.012 --> 05:37.747
Nothing.

05:37.748 --> 05:40.016
It's just my sister
hasn't seen him in a while,

05:40.017 --> 05:41.384
they'll have a great time.

05:41.385 --> 05:43.386
She's super responsible.

05:43.387 --> 05:45.754
Ha! And I'm not?

05:46.923 --> 05:49.258
Uh-oh, she's going to laugh again.

05:50.160 --> 05:51.895
No, Oscar.

05:51.896 --> 05:54.131
It's just I like Evan a whole lot,

05:54.132 --> 05:56.399
and I'd like to keep him...

05:56.400 --> 05:58.568
Well, I'd like to keep him.

05:58.569 --> 05:59.703
I can do this.

05:59.704 --> 06:01.071
We won't leave the building,

06:01.072 --> 06:04.474
I'll never take my eyes off
of him and you can trust me.

06:04.475 --> 06:06.243
You trust me, right?

06:06.244 --> 06:07.644
Okay.

06:07.645 --> 06:09.179
Let's give it a try.

06:09.180 --> 06:10.647
Awesome!

06:10.648 --> 06:12.348
We're gonna have a great time!

06:15.819 --> 06:18.187
And be very responsible.

