06:28.973 --> 06:30.448
Who are you?

06:30.449 --> 06:32.950
Mozart van Beethoven?

06:34.251 --> 06:36.391
Our educational system
really failed you, didn't it?

06:37.354 --> 06:38.863
This is my costume

06:38.864 --> 06:40.198
for tonight's terrifying trek

06:40.199 --> 06:42.534
through our building's haunted past.

06:42.535 --> 06:44.502
Oh great, do you mind
if Evan and I tag along?

06:44.503 --> 06:45.570
I would love that!

06:45.571 --> 06:47.171
I just didn't think you were interested.

06:47.195 --> 06:49.028
Oh, I'm not.

06:50.109 --> 06:52.310
But if I want to have any
kind of future with Charlotte,

06:52.311 --> 06:54.345
I need to prove to her that I'm mature.

06:54.346 --> 06:55.647
So I'm going to spend Halloween

06:55.648 --> 06:57.115
with the most mature guy I know.

06:57.116 --> 06:58.783
Well, thank you, Oscar.

06:58.784 --> 07:02.419
And when I say mature, I mean boring.

07:04.055 --> 07:05.356
Oh, you might be surprised.

07:05.357 --> 07:08.191
This tour is going
to be "spook-tacular."

07:09.928 --> 07:11.528
"Abso-boo-tly" frightening.

07:12.764 --> 07:13.765
For all the...

07:13.766 --> 07:16.833
ghouls.

07:17.902 --> 07:20.470
It's exhausting being you, isn't it?

07:21.639 --> 07:23.408
It's not easy.

07:23.409 --> 07:25.844
Hey Oscar, go long!

07:25.845 --> 07:26.845
Hey!

07:28.914 --> 07:30.381
Nice catch!

07:30.382 --> 07:31.382
Thanks.

07:31.383 --> 07:33.317
Wish I was wearing a cup.

07:34.886 --> 07:36.921
Teddy, what's with the suitcase?

07:36.922 --> 07:38.256
Oh, it's Andre's.

07:38.257 --> 07:39.520
His second costume is in there.

07:39.521 --> 07:42.093
I hit all the apartments
in this costume,

07:42.094 --> 07:43.595
then I change for round two.

07:43.596 --> 07:44.863
Very clever.

07:44.864 --> 07:46.630
It's not my first Halloween.

07:48.066 --> 07:49.889
If he was this focused
on sports or education,

07:49.890 --> 07:51.269
he'd be unstoppable.

07:51.270 --> 07:54.004
Can you imagine?

07:55.273 --> 07:57.208
Well, I'm off. See ya, Dad.

07:57.209 --> 07:59.277
You sure you don't
want me to go with you?

07:59.278 --> 08:01.779
No offense, but you slow me down.

08:01.780 --> 08:03.214
Too much chit-chat,

08:03.215 --> 08:04.548
not enough Kit Kat.

08:05.316 --> 08:06.499
Now who's this cute little...

08:06.500 --> 08:08.666
No time!

08:11.155 --> 08:12.523
All right, I'm ready to go, Oscar.

08:12.524 --> 08:13.591
Great!

08:13.592 --> 08:14.626
I'll be home by 10:00.

08:14.627 --> 08:16.427
Be responsible, follow the rules.

08:16.428 --> 08:17.428
I will.

08:17.429 --> 08:18.463
I was talking to Oscar.

08:18.464 --> 08:20.198
I will.

08:20.199 --> 08:21.633
We're going to have so much fun.

08:21.634 --> 08:23.134
Well, don't have too much fun.

08:23.135 --> 08:25.236
We'll be with Felix.

08:27.439 --> 08:29.173
Well, have some fun.

08:29.174 --> 08:30.407
Okay.

08:31.609 --> 08:33.311
Good evening.

08:33.312 --> 08:36.614
Our Haunted History tour will
begin when the clock strikes...

08:36.615 --> 08:38.782
6:45.

08:40.585 --> 08:43.354
Doing this for Charlotte,
doing this for Charlotte...

08:43.355 --> 08:45.323
Oscar, it's funny.

08:45.324 --> 08:47.467
Tonight you are attempting
to act like a mature adult,

08:47.468 --> 08:49.427
while I'm endeavoring
to access my inner child.

08:49.428 --> 08:52.530
Oh, he's probably just in there dusting.

08:52.531 --> 08:54.232
Hello, Felix.

08:54.233 --> 08:56.334
This is my son Simon.

08:56.335 --> 08:58.102
No, I'm Albert Einstein.

08:58.103 --> 08:59.103
Of course you are.

08:59.104 --> 09:01.205
And you can meet us back here in an hour

09:01.206 --> 09:03.908
because the tour is
"relativit-ly" short.

09:03.909 --> 09:06.844
Good one.

09:06.845 --> 09:08.646
I have a backpack of supplies.

09:08.647 --> 09:10.381
Breath spray, wet wipes,

09:10.382 --> 09:12.483
and a drone if we need to send for help.

09:12.484 --> 09:15.652
Oh, my god, there's two of them?

09:17.088 --> 09:19.023
Oscar, can we go up to the roof?

09:19.024 --> 09:21.367
All my friends are gonna sneak
up and throw water balloons!

09:21.368 --> 09:22.860
That's an awesome idea!

09:22.861 --> 09:25.096
Is what a bad adult would say...

09:25.097 --> 09:27.831
to an awesome idea
that I can't let you do.

09:32.805 --> 09:37.542
Oh hello, I am Ebenezer Strotham.

09:37.543 --> 09:39.844
You may not know me,
but you do know my work.

09:39.845 --> 09:42.012
You're standing in it.

09:44.582 --> 09:46.484
The building.

09:46.485 --> 09:47.885
I designed the building.

09:47.886 --> 09:51.556
In 1905, it was the site
of a mysterious death.

09:51.557 --> 09:54.359
Robert Coleman's heart gave out
in his seventh-floor apartment.

09:54.360 --> 09:58.863
Authorities called it natural causes,

09:58.864 --> 10:01.031
but some called it...

10:02.967 --> 10:04.202
...murder!

10:06.972 --> 10:08.235
How long is this going to take?

10:08.236 --> 10:09.340
About an hour.

10:09.341 --> 10:11.576
But it'll feel like forever.

10:11.577 --> 10:13.478
That's relativity!

10:13.479 --> 10:15.613
Hold your fire.

10:15.614 --> 10:17.015
So join me now

10:17.016 --> 10:18.416
for an evening of mystery,

10:18.417 --> 10:20.518
but, most of all, fun.

10:21.520 --> 10:22.520
Not a toy!

10:22.521 --> 10:24.654
Not a toy!

10:28.993 --> 10:31.295
Now, Robert Coleman didn't
die in that stairwell.

10:31.296 --> 10:33.531
But he could have,
because safety railings

10:33.532 --> 10:35.700
weren't required by
New York state until...

10:35.701 --> 10:37.868
...1937.

10:39.037 --> 10:42.073
So how did they navigate the stairs?

10:42.074 --> 10:44.040
They walked, Einstein.

10:44.876 --> 10:46.944
What? He's Einstein.

10:46.945 --> 10:48.346
Join me as we enter

10:48.347 --> 10:51.682
the apartment where Coleman
lived with his kindly nurse.

10:51.683 --> 10:53.083
Lived...

10:54.252 --> 10:56.419
...and died!

10:58.456 --> 11:00.258
Come on, come on, come on.

11:00.259 --> 11:02.425
Go, go, go, go, go.

11:06.697 --> 11:10.468
Who dares disturb our slumber?

11:10.469 --> 11:11.669
You want some slumber,

11:11.670 --> 11:14.504
why don't you join our tour?

11:15.406 --> 11:17.041
You're not a guy,

11:17.042 --> 11:19.444
you're the lady who keeps
trying to sell my mom jewelry.

11:19.445 --> 11:25.048
Tell her that all the seasonal
bracelets are half price.

11:26.144 --> 11:27.327
Stay on script.

11:27.328 --> 11:30.455
I roam the halls

11:30.456 --> 11:33.357
looking for a young, healthy heart

11:33.358 --> 11:38.228
because mine was taken from
me on a night most foul.

11:40.465 --> 11:44.001
Might I be the murderer?

11:44.002 --> 11:46.104
Who's the hooker?

11:46.105 --> 11:48.905
Watch your mouth, 4B. I know your mama.

11:49.801 --> 11:51.184
Dani, I didn't tell you

11:51.185 --> 11:52.410
to buy a sexy nurse outfit.

11:52.411 --> 11:54.078
I just bought a nurse's outfit.

11:54.079 --> 11:55.645
I put the sexy in it.

11:57.215 --> 11:59.650
Well, kids, it's still
pretty scary, isn't it?

11:59.651 --> 12:01.385
Please, this is nothing.

12:01.386 --> 12:02.854
Did you ever see Saw?

12:02.855 --> 12:04.322
See saw?

12:04.323 --> 12:07.425
Oh no, if those things aren't
balanced it's like a catapult.

12:07.426 --> 12:08.793
Can we go now?

12:08.794 --> 12:10.027
Yes, because there are

12:10.028 --> 12:12.630
17 clues hidden throughout the building

12:12.631 --> 12:15.999
that will help solve the mystery.

12:17.301 --> 12:20.738
Did she say 17?

12:20.739 --> 12:21.973
I wasn't listening.

12:21.974 --> 12:23.139
Yeah, me neither.

12:24.108 --> 12:26.144
And that's why in mid-1990s

12:26.145 --> 12:28.679
they replaced every
carpet in the building.

12:28.680 --> 12:30.448
Remember, children:

12:30.449 --> 12:32.616
mold is the silent killer.

12:33.784 --> 12:36.721
Excuse me, my mom just texted me.

12:36.722 --> 12:37.955
I have to go.

12:37.956 --> 12:40.725
Yeah, his mom said I have to go, too.

12:40.726 --> 12:41.893
Yeah, you know, me too.

12:41.894 --> 12:42.894
Hey, wait!

12:42.895 --> 12:44.028
Come on, Oscar!

12:44.029 --> 12:45.696
You promised that we
would have some fun.

12:45.697 --> 12:47.532
We will. I'll talk to Felix.

12:47.533 --> 12:49.167
Felix?

12:49.168 --> 12:50.968
Felix?

12:50.969 --> 12:51.969
Ebenezer?

12:51.970 --> 12:53.337
Yes?

12:53.338 --> 12:55.642
We gotta speed things along.
These kids are getting bored.

12:55.643 --> 12:56.241
Bored?

12:56.242 --> 12:58.910
Or entertained into silence?

12:58.911 --> 13:01.379
It's Halloween, all we want is candy!

13:01.380 --> 13:02.680
I mean all they want is candy.

13:02.681 --> 13:04.015
And they're going to get it.

13:04.016 --> 13:05.316
The 17th clue is the combination

13:05.317 --> 13:07.084
that unlocks this
briefcase full of candy.

13:07.085 --> 13:08.653
You've been holding out on us?!

13:08.654 --> 13:09.820
- Give it!
- No, no.

13:09.821 --> 13:11.355
- Give it!
- No.

13:11.356 --> 13:12.390
Man, those Pilates

13:12.391 --> 13:13.558
are really paying off.

13:13.559 --> 13:14.759
Thank you, thank you very much.

13:14.760 --> 13:16.081
But you're not getting the candy!

13:16.082 --> 13:17.945
Stop being so immature.
You stop being so lame!

13:17.946 --> 13:19.497
We're going to lose these kids!

13:19.498 --> 13:22.033
Oh crap, I've already lost one!

13:22.034 --> 13:22.934
Evan! Evan!

13:22.935 --> 13:25.036
Evan!

13:25.037 --> 13:27.205
Have you seen a chimpbot?

13:27.206 --> 13:29.340
I'm a T Rex!

13:29.341 --> 13:31.508
Do you know how questions work?

13:33.878 --> 13:35.146
There you are, buddy.

13:35.147 --> 13:36.914
Listen, we gotta stick together.

13:36.915 --> 13:38.783
Let's go back to my
apartment and regroup.

13:38.784 --> 13:40.685
We've got a ton of candy over there.

13:40.686 --> 13:42.686
There's a chimpbot.

13:43.754 --> 13:45.188
There's a reason you're extinct.

13:46.224 --> 13:48.626
Candy is right there, help yourself.

13:48.627 --> 13:49.760
Evan ditched me.

13:49.761 --> 13:51.229
I thought I lost him for a second.

13:51.230 --> 13:52.396
That would have been bad.

13:52.397 --> 13:53.864
He's Charlotte's only kid.

13:55.767 --> 13:56.767
You're not Evan!

13:56.768 --> 13:58.569
Why are you in his costume?

13:58.570 --> 14:00.004
This is my back-up.

14:00.005 --> 14:02.473
Why didn't you tell me when
I kept calling you Evan!

14:02.474 --> 14:04.254
You promised me candy
and I rolled with it.

14:06.577 --> 14:09.146
Teddy, stop drinking alone
and help me find Evan!

14:09.147 --> 14:10.648
I'm going to start in the lobby.

14:10.649 --> 14:13.017
I'll start at the
penthouse and work down.

14:13.018 --> 14:14.385
I'll just hang back here.

14:14.386 --> 14:16.254
My dogs are barking.

14:16.255 --> 14:17.554
Oh, great.

14:26.182 --> 14:28.749
Well, it's just us.

14:29.834 --> 14:31.868
I suppose we ought to call it a night.

14:31.869 --> 14:33.536
Really?

14:33.537 --> 14:36.773
But I have to know... was it murder?

14:36.774 --> 14:39.641
No, it was complications of an STD.

14:41.378 --> 14:45.147
Which stands for "Super
Terrifying Disease."

14:46.476 --> 14:47.796
Now that I've spoiled the ending,

14:47.797 --> 14:49.980
I suppose there's no reason
to do the rest of the tour.

14:49.981 --> 14:51.655
Where the hell are they?!

14:51.656 --> 14:53.456
We're clue number seven!

14:53.457 --> 14:54.840
They should have been here by now.

14:54.841 --> 14:56.059
They better hurry up.

14:56.060 --> 14:58.395
This place is creepy,
and the radiator steam

14:58.396 --> 15:00.562
is making my damn nails pop off.

15:01.898 --> 15:04.401
Well I suppose you deserve a reward

15:04.402 --> 15:06.101
for staying as long as you did.

15:08.772 --> 15:10.939
Do you have anything healthy?

15:15.679 --> 15:17.713
Granny Smith. Jackpot!

15:22.445 --> 15:24.028
I'm sorry that I ruined your Halloween.

15:24.029 --> 15:25.755
That's okay.

15:25.756 --> 15:27.257
I don't like Halloween.

15:27.258 --> 15:28.692
I can't wait to be an adult

15:28.693 --> 15:30.560
so I don't have to
do this stuff anymore.

15:30.561 --> 15:34.764
You know, I suppose I felt that
way too when I was your age.

15:34.765 --> 15:37.734
But now I feel like I
missed out on something.

15:37.735 --> 15:41.904
I see people cutting loose,
and being mischievous...

15:43.973 --> 15:46.876
I wish I had learned how to do that.

15:46.877 --> 15:48.078
Yeah?

15:48.079 --> 15:49.611
Yeah.

15:50.547 --> 15:52.415
You have plenty of time to be an adult,

15:52.416 --> 15:55.451
so don't rush through the kid part.

15:58.021 --> 16:00.190
You know, Simon?

16:00.191 --> 16:03.059
Simon?

16:03.060 --> 16:04.226
- Dr. Einstein?
- Yes?

16:09.566 --> 16:11.835
What do you say you and
I have some fun, huh?

16:11.836 --> 16:12.899
Throw caution to the wind!

16:12.900 --> 16:15.066
Not the wind?!

16:16.573 --> 16:17.841
Yes, the wind!

16:17.842 --> 16:19.442
I don't know how to do that.

16:19.443 --> 16:20.744
Neither do I.

16:20.745 --> 16:24.381
But we will brave these
uncharted waters together, hm?

16:24.382 --> 16:25.782
Come on.

16:25.783 --> 16:27.117
Oh wait, wait, wait.

16:27.118 --> 16:29.141
There's a little bit of
food residue on your shirt.

16:29.142 --> 16:30.019
Oh dear.

16:30.020 --> 16:31.788
Boop!

16:31.789 --> 16:33.989
- This might take some time.
- Yeah.

16:35.392 --> 16:37.559
I lost a human, a whole human!

16:41.632 --> 16:43.500
Well that's an ego boost.

16:43.501 --> 16:45.902
I didn't think you'd be home so soon.

16:45.903 --> 16:47.170
I was able to duck out early

16:47.171 --> 16:48.994
so the three of us could
go trick-or-treating.

16:48.995 --> 16:50.740
Oh, you really didn't have to do that.

16:50.741 --> 16:53.209
You really, really didn't have to.

16:53.210 --> 16:55.211
Okay, here's the thing.

16:55.212 --> 16:56.346
Evan...

16:56.347 --> 16:58.348
Is right there!

16:58.349 --> 16:59.416
Yeah, Oscar,

16:59.417 --> 17:00.984
right here where you dropped me off.

17:00.985 --> 17:03.686
I told my mom you did
a great job watching me.

17:03.687 --> 17:05.054
I'm glad it went well.

17:05.055 --> 17:07.257
Yes...

17:07.258 --> 17:10.192
It went well.

17:10.859 --> 17:12.362
I'm going to leave now.

17:12.363 --> 17:14.696
Well, thanks for doing such
a good job watching him.

17:14.698 --> 17:16.633
I didn't do a good job watching him.

17:16.634 --> 17:18.101
He ran away!

17:18.102 --> 17:19.435
What?!

17:19.436 --> 17:21.905
I've been looking all
over the building for you!

17:21.906 --> 17:23.373
You scared the hell out of me!

17:23.374 --> 17:25.840
Look, I'm sweating even more than usual!

17:27.109 --> 17:28.778
Is this true, Evan?

17:28.779 --> 17:30.879
He is pretty sweaty.

17:32.782 --> 17:34.050
Sorry.

17:34.051 --> 17:35.351
He wasn't any fun.

17:35.352 --> 17:37.287
Oh, I was no fun?

17:37.288 --> 17:40.790
You want to see me being no fun?

17:40.791 --> 17:42.991
How about no food for a month?

17:45.328 --> 17:47.297
Might be a little much.

17:47.298 --> 17:49.132
Yeah, you're right, it's my first time.

17:49.133 --> 17:52.401
No Chimpocalypse for a month.

17:53.069 --> 17:54.304
That sounds fair.

17:54.305 --> 17:55.805
No, it doesn't.

17:55.806 --> 17:58.407
Man, Oscar, you're so mean!

18:05.215 --> 18:06.749
It's not easy, is it?

18:06.750 --> 18:10.220
No, how do you do this
parenting thing 24/7?

18:10.221 --> 18:12.387
Wine helps.

18:13.356 --> 18:14.958
But you know what?

18:14.959 --> 18:16.793
You handled that really well.

18:16.794 --> 18:17.827
You think?

18:17.828 --> 18:18.828
Yes.

18:18.829 --> 18:20.563
Very mature.

18:20.564 --> 18:23.533
And that's quite a sacrifice for you,

18:23.534 --> 18:26.169
no Chimpocalypse for a month?

18:26.170 --> 18:27.203
What?

18:27.204 --> 18:28.304
No, that was for Evan.

18:28.305 --> 18:30.439
He ran away, not me.

18:31.975 --> 18:34.177
I gotta say, Oscar, seeing you step up

18:34.178 --> 18:38.313
like you did there was pretty sexy.

18:45.788 --> 18:47.323
You want that candy don't you?

18:47.324 --> 18:48.557
Yeah, I really do.

18:52.362 --> 18:53.363
There you all are!

18:56.200 --> 18:58.201
You left before the most fun part...

18:58.202 --> 19:01.938
reading material!

19:01.939 --> 19:03.339
You want to talk about scary,

19:03.340 --> 19:04.707
wait 'til you see these

19:04.708 --> 19:06.341
archaic building codes.

19:07.143 --> 19:07.844
What?

19:07.845 --> 19:09.312
What? What is it?

19:10.514 --> 19:12.849
It's the ghost of Robert Coleman!

19:12.850 --> 19:14.284
He's come for

19:14.285 --> 19:16.251
my heart!

19:17.153 --> 19:18.187
Ah!

19:23.793 --> 19:27.630
Respect... your... teachers.

19:34.137 --> 19:35.772
That was awesome!

19:35.773 --> 19:37.407
Yes, it was!

19:37.408 --> 19:39.042
Great work with the drone!

19:39.043 --> 19:41.544
That was exactly the kind
of reckless tomfoolery

19:41.545 --> 19:43.679
that being a kid is all about, huh?

19:47.617 --> 19:50.019
I guess we better get you home, huh?

19:50.020 --> 19:53.188
Why do I get the nagging feeling
that I'm forgetting something?

19:55.191 --> 19:57.526
Please tell me your foot has a tail.

19:59.662 --> 20:01.598
I felt it, too!

20:01.599 --> 20:03.665
- Aw, hell no!
- Oh, my god!

20:12.854 --> 20:14.654
This is the first time
ever having nougat.

20:16.157 --> 20:17.959
Good.

20:17.960 --> 20:19.125
Not great.

20:20.328 --> 20:22.163
All right, here, try
a Three Musketeers bar.

20:22.164 --> 20:24.899
They named a candy bar
after my third-favorite

20:24.900 --> 20:27.067
Alexandre Dumas novel!

20:29.504 --> 20:30.638
No, I probably shouldn't.

20:30.639 --> 20:31.906
I've had so much already.

20:31.907 --> 20:34.041
Oh come on, feed your inner child.

20:34.042 --> 20:35.243
He's had a huge night.

20:35.244 --> 20:37.311
Should we split it?

20:37.312 --> 20:38.695
Unless of course you're too mature

20:38.696 --> 20:40.279
and responsible for candy after dinner.

20:40.280 --> 20:41.182
Who knows?

20:41.183 --> 20:43.483
I may even floss tonight.

20:45.086 --> 20:46.687
Whoo! What a night.

20:46.688 --> 20:48.356
Look at that swagger!

20:48.357 --> 20:50.524
Learned it from me.

20:51.392 --> 20:53.326
Let's get you home, son.

20:59.867 --> 21:02.035
One of you chumps want
to tell me something?

